06:36.600 --> 06:38.065
GOOD MORNING.

06:38.067 --> 06:40.365
WELL, GOOD NEWS.

06:43.267 --> 06:44.798
WHAT'S THAT, PERCY?

06:44.800 --> 06:47.132
WHEN I DIDN'T HEAR YOU STIRRING
IN YOUR ROOM THIS MORNING,

06:47.134 --> 06:50.065
I RAN DOWN TO THE OFFICE,
CHECKED THE OBITUARIES

06:50.067 --> 06:51.432
TO SEE
IF YOU WEREN'T IN IT.

06:52.867 --> 06:55.132
WELL, I'M SORRY
IF I WORRIED YOU.

06:55.134 --> 06:56.132
DIDN'T GET TO SLEEP

06:56.134 --> 06:57.932
TILL WELL AFTER 3:00
IN THE MORNING.

06:59.267 --> 07:01.132
YOU HAVING
SECOND THOUGHTS?

07:01.134 --> 07:02.999
ABOUT WHAT?

07:03.001 --> 07:06.199
FINALLY MOVING OUT OF
THAT HARRIDAN'S LAIR?

07:06.201 --> 07:07.332
NOT AT ALL.

07:07.334 --> 07:10.065
WELL, IF YOU ARE,
IT'S OKAY.

07:10.067 --> 07:12.698
YOU KNOW,
WHEN I LEFT JOANNE,

07:12.700 --> 07:14.432
I CRIED LIKE A BABY.

07:14.434 --> 07:18.732
WHEN I LEFT LOU ELLEN,
IT WASN'T NOTHING.

07:18.734 --> 07:22.465
BUT THEN I LEFT RHONDA AND
IT WAS WORSE THAN JOANNE.

07:22.467 --> 07:23.865
COULDN'T GET OUT OF BED.

07:23.867 --> 07:26.998
THOUGHT I WAS HAVING
A HEART ATTACK.

07:27.000 --> 07:30.198
DOCTOR TOLD ME IT WAS PANIC
ATTACKS, BUT I FELT IT,

07:30.200 --> 07:32.165
I FELT IT IN MY HEART.

07:32.167 --> 07:35.565
WELL, MY HEART'S TICKING
JUST FINE, THANK YOU.

07:35.567 --> 07:37.065
WELL, YOU A BETTER MAN
THAN ME.

07:37.067 --> 07:39.699
THE COMPARISONS ARE ODIOUS,

07:39.701 --> 07:42.532
BUT I WON'T DISAGREE.

07:42.534 --> 07:44.132
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

07:44.134 --> 07:45.199
MISS HUNTER, CAN YOU
TELL US WHAT HAPPENED

07:45.201 --> 07:46.865
THE NIGHT OF THE MURDER?

07:46.867 --> 07:48.465
-STAY CLOSE TO ME.
-MY CLIENT HAS NO COMMENT.

07:48.467 --> 07:49.932
THANK YOU, EVERYBODY.

07:49.934 --> 07:51.398
YOU ARE ACCUSED OF KILLING
YOUR HUSBAND IN HIS SLEEP.

07:51.400 --> 07:52.732
-MAKE SOME ROOM.
-HOW IS THAT SELF-DEFENSE?

07:52.734 --> 07:53.798
DON'T ANSWER THAT,
COME ON, COME ON.

07:53.800 --> 07:55.198
HOW ARE YOUR
CHILDREN RESPONDING?

07:55.200 --> 07:56.398
YOU KNOW THEY HAVEN'T
LET ME TALK TO THEM

07:56.400 --> 07:57.665
SINCE I WAS ARRESTED.

07:57.667 --> 07:59.332
JUST KEEP MOVING
AND BE QUIET, OKAY?

07:59.334 --> 08:01.998
YEAH, OKAY, I'LL TAKE A FEW
QUESTIONS EVERYBODY, ALL RIGHT.

08:02.000 --> 08:04.265
-WHO'S THIS?
-ROCHELLE CROSS.

08:04.267 --> 08:05.665
SHE'S WITH THE LEGAL
DEFENSE FUND.

08:05.667 --> 08:07.398
SHE RAISED THE MONEY
TO BAIL YOU OUT.

08:07.400 --> 08:09.199
THANK YOU.

08:09.201 --> 08:10.531
THEY DON'T UNDERSTAND.

08:10.533 --> 08:11.765
NO, THEY DON'T.

08:11.767 --> 08:13.765
WE'RE GONNA FIX THAT.

08:13.767 --> 08:15.965
[ REPORTERS ALL TALKING
AT ONCE ]

08:19.000 --> 08:21.165
ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU.

08:21.167 --> 08:24.865
CALL IF YOU HEAR, THOUGH.

08:24.867 --> 08:28.465
HEY, AND THANK YOU FOR
TAKING MY CALL.

08:28.467 --> 08:29.732
GOODBYE.

08:29.734 --> 08:31.998
HIS PARENTS DON'T
KNOW WHERE THEY ARE.

08:32.000 --> 08:33.332
HIS THINGS ARE GONE,
BUT HE'S BEEN THERE

08:33.334 --> 08:35.732
FOR THE LAST THREE WEEKS,
SO WHO KNOWS.

08:35.734 --> 08:37.599
CAN I KEEP THIS?

08:37.601 --> 08:39.931
HEY, WHY DON'T WE JUST
GET YOU A NEW ONE?

08:39.933 --> 08:41.465
JACOB,
MY DAUGHTER IS GONE.

08:41.467 --> 08:44.065
I'M NOT GOING
PHONE SHOPPING.

08:44.067 --> 08:45.732
WHERE ARE YOU GOING ANYWAY?

08:45.734 --> 08:46.932
TO HIS PARENTS' HOUSE.

08:46.934 --> 08:48.332
DIDN'T THEY JUST
SAY HE WASN'T THERE?

08:48.334 --> 08:49.732
WELL,
THEY MIGHT COME BACK.

08:49.734 --> 08:52.665
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO DO, JACOB, NOTHING?

08:52.667 --> 08:54.199
THAT BOY COULD KILL HER.

08:54.201 --> 08:56.198
I TRIED TO STOP HIM
AND YOU WOULDN'T LET ME.

08:56.200 --> 08:58.398
BECAUSE YOU'D JUST
MAKE THINGS WORSE

08:58.400 --> 09:00.332
WITH ALL
OF YOUR VIOLENCE.

09:00.334 --> 09:02.865
WE DON'T NEED
ANYMORE FIGHTING.

09:02.867 --> 09:04.398
WELL, WHATEVER YOUR
PLAN IS, I'M HER FATHER,

09:04.400 --> 09:06.332
YOU NEED TO INCLUDE ME.
YOU CAN'T JUST ICE ME OUT.

09:06.334 --> 09:07.665
NOW, MY SON HAS A POINT.

09:07.667 --> 09:09.231
NOW, MAE, NOW, YOU JUST
STAY OUT OF THIS

09:09.233 --> 09:11.565
'CAUSE I TOLD YOU YOU WERE
BEING TOO HARD ON HER.

09:11.567 --> 09:12.665
NOW LOOK WHAT'S HAPPENED.

09:12.667 --> 09:14.465
JUST BACK OFF!

09:14.467 --> 09:17.598
I'M NOT GONNA LET
ZORA TURN INTO FAITH.

09:17.600 --> 09:18.765
I WON'T DO THAT.

09:18.767 --> 09:20.331
WHY WOULD YOU SAY
SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

09:20.333 --> 09:21.465
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'M SORRY.

09:21.467 --> 09:22.998
MOM, JUST, JUST,
SHE DIDN'T MEAN IT.

09:23.000 --> 09:25.598
I'LL CALL IF I SEE HER.

09:25.600 --> 09:26.798
I'M COMING WITH YOU.

09:26.800 --> 09:28.399
DO YOU REMEMBER
HOW HARD IT WAS

09:28.401 --> 09:30.598
FOR US TO KEEP THEM FROM
CALLING THE COPS ON YOU BEFORE?

09:30.600 --> 09:34.231
JUST STAY OUT OF IT,
PLEASE, JACOB.

09:34.233 --> 09:37.865
GIVE ME MY PHONE.

09:37.867 --> 09:40.865
TAKE YOUR PHONE!

09:40.867 --> 09:44.798
I WILL TAKE YOU OVER THERE.

09:44.800 --> 09:46.065
THANK YOU.

09:46.067 --> 09:56.198
♪♪

09:56.200 --> 09:58.265
WELL, IT'S A BIG
DAY FOR YOU, HUH?

09:58.267 --> 10:00.131
YEAH, I GOT SERVICES
AT 10:00, 2:00, 4:00.

10:00.133 --> 10:02.598
HEY, COME HERE, COME
HERE, COME HERE.

10:02.600 --> 10:05.398
UH, THAT'S GOOD NEWS,
I GUESS.

10:05.400 --> 10:06.932
YEAH, I DO HAVE BILLS
TO PAY.

10:06.934 --> 10:08.998
HEY, DADDY,
SORRY I'M LATE, PERCY.

10:09.000 --> 10:11.465
IT WAS BIG DRAMA AT
THE HOUSE THIS MORNING.

10:11.467 --> 10:13.198
HEY, W-WHAT KIND OF DRAMA?

10:13.200 --> 10:14.998
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT IT, DADDY.

10:15.000 --> 10:17.331
HEY!

10:17.333 --> 10:19.398
I'M STILL YOUR FATHER.

10:19.400 --> 10:20.865
WHAT KIND OF DRAMA?

10:20.867 --> 10:23.865
JAMES, WE HAVE EVERYTHING
UNDER CONTROL.

10:23.867 --> 10:25.698
YES, CHARITY TOLD ME
WHAT HAPPENED.

10:25.700 --> 10:27.032
I FIGURED OUT THAT PART,

10:27.034 --> 10:29.965
BUT KERISSA AND I ARE
REALLY HANDLING EVERYTHING.

10:29.967 --> 10:31.532
THERE'S NOTHING
FOR YOU TO DO.

10:31.534 --> 10:32.732
DID WE CALL THE POLICE?

10:32.734 --> 10:34.599
SHE'S AN ADULT NOW,
THEY'RE BOTH ADULTS.

10:34.601 --> 10:35.865
IT'S NOT A CRIME.

10:35.867 --> 10:38.098
EVEN SO, JACOB SHOULD
CALL THAT FRIEND OF HIS,

10:38.100 --> 10:39.699
THE DEPUTY MAYOR.

10:39.701 --> 10:41.431
KERISSA AND I ARE HEADED TO
THE PARENTS' HOUSE RIGHT NOW

10:41.433 --> 10:42.832
TO SEE
IF WE CAN CATCH HIM.

10:42.834 --> 10:45.365
This is not going
to be a quick fix.

10:45.367 --> 10:50.499
AND RESIST THE URGE TO
MAKE MEANINGLESS ACTIVITY.

10:53.634 --> 10:55.432
OH, LORD.

10:57.501 --> 10:59.832
WHAT'D SHE SAY?

10:59.834 --> 11:02.132
THE MOTHERS
ARE HANDLING IT.

11:18.067 --> 11:22.332
DO YOU WANT US TO STAY WITH
YOU FOR A LITTLE WHILE?

11:22.334 --> 11:24.732
NO, IT'S OKAY.

11:24.734 --> 11:26.399
THANK YOU, THOUGH.

11:39.734 --> 11:41.932
IT'S GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, DARLING.

11:41.934 --> 11:43.665
WE'RE GONNA REPLACE
THAT SCRAWNY BOY YOU HAD

11:43.667 --> 11:45.198
WITH A BEAST
OF AN ATTORNEY.

11:45.200 --> 11:49.332
YOU JUST WATCH,
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.

11:49.334 --> 11:53.198
I KNOW, I JUST NEED TO
SEE MY KIDS, YOU KNOW.

11:53.200 --> 11:55.598
I ASKED THAT LAWYER IF
HE COULD GET THE JUDGE

11:55.600 --> 11:58.265
TO AT LEAST LET ME CALL
THEM, HE WOULDN'T EVEN ASK.

11:58.267 --> 11:59.932
I'M NOT SURE THERE'S
MUCH ANYONE CAN DO

11:59.934 --> 12:01.465
WITH THEM IN FOSTER CARE.

12:01.467 --> 12:02.532
I KNOW SOMEBODY
OVER AT CPS

12:02.534 --> 12:05.065
MAY BE ABLE TO HELP
YOU FIND THEM ANYHOW.

12:05.067 --> 12:06.598
WOULD YOU DO THAT,
PLEASE?

12:06.600 --> 12:08.132
I'LL CALL THEM RIGHT NOW.

12:08.134 --> 12:10.465
THANK YOU.

12:10.467 --> 12:12.198
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

12:12.200 --> 12:13.932
GET SOME REST, CORALIE.

12:13.934 --> 12:16.765
I'LL CALL YOU IF I HEAR
ANYTHING BACK, ALL RIGHT?

12:16.767 --> 12:20.198
PROMISE.

12:20.200 --> 12:21.765
[ KEYS JINGLING ]

12:24.234 --> 12:27.365
WHO DO YOU KNOW
AT CPS?

12:27.367 --> 12:29.098
I'VE GOT A FRIEND.

12:29.100 --> 12:34.932
♪♪

12:45.867 --> 12:48.932
Kerissa: THAT'S THEIR HOUSE
RIGHT THERE.

12:48.934 --> 12:51.132
I WOULD LIKE TO GIVE
THOSE PARENTS OF HIS

12:51.134 --> 12:52.465
A PIECE OF MY MIND.

12:52.467 --> 12:53.798
TALKING SMACK
AGAINST MY SON

12:53.800 --> 12:55.398
WHEN THEIR BOY'S
SUCH A MENACE.

12:55.400 --> 12:56.798
PLEASE DON'T.

12:56.800 --> 12:59.132
LISTEN, ANY FATHER WOULD HAVE
WHACKED THAT BOY, KERISSA,

12:59.134 --> 13:00.665
ESPECIALLY GIVEN
WHAT HE DID.

13:00.667 --> 13:04.732
I KNOW, BUT CAN WE
JUST, PLEASE JUST...

13:07.067 --> 13:10.598
ALL RIGHT, FINE, I WILL
JUST LEAVE THEM TO JESUS.

13:10.600 --> 13:14.065
THEY WILL BE DEALT WITH.

13:14.067 --> 13:15.532
I DON'T SEE THEIR CAR.

13:15.534 --> 13:17.398
WELL, WE CAN JUST STAY HERE
FOR A LITTLE WHILE, RIGHT?

13:17.400 --> 13:19.732
AS LONG AS YOU LIKE.

13:23.667 --> 13:26.198
IF YOU THINK I DIDN'T
DO EVERYTHING I COULD

13:26.200 --> 13:29.465
TO GET MY DAUGHTER
BACK HOME...

13:29.467 --> 13:32.132
I'M SORRY I SAID THAT, MAE.
I WAS UPSET.

13:32.134 --> 13:35.865
I STILL AM, BUT...

13:35.867 --> 13:38.898
I'M SORRY.

13:38.900 --> 13:40.965
WE ALL HAVE THIS
THING INSIDE US

13:40.967 --> 13:46.865
THAT WANTS TO BELIEVE THAT
WE CAN FIX IT, YOU KNOW.

13:46.867 --> 13:48.665
WHATEVER OUR CHILDREN
ARE GOING THROUGH,

13:48.667 --> 13:52.765
THEIR SUFFERING,
WE THINK WE CAN FIX IT.

13:54.800 --> 13:56.999
BUT SOME GET AWAY.

14:00.067 --> 14:02.665
I WON'T LET
THAT HAPPEN TO ZORA.

14:02.667 --> 14:05.165
YOU MIGHT NOT
HAVE A CHOICE.

14:09.600 --> 14:10.665
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

14:10.667 --> 14:13.198
COME ON IN.

14:13.200 --> 14:13.932
HEY.

14:13.934 --> 14:15.332
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

14:15.334 --> 14:16.932
OH, THAT WAS JUST ME.

14:16.934 --> 14:18.465
I WAS WONDERING
WHERE YOU'VE BEEN.

14:18.467 --> 14:21.532
I WAS BEGINNING TO THINK
YOU WERE MAD ABOUT SOMETHING

14:21.534 --> 14:23.265
OR SOMETHING CRAZY.

14:23.267 --> 14:27.332
NO, IT WASN'T THAT.
ZORA LEFT.

14:27.334 --> 14:28.398
LEFT WHERE?

14:28.400 --> 14:30.032
MY MOTHER'S WITH ISAIAH.

14:30.034 --> 14:32.032
SHE TURNED 18,
AND SHE TOOK OFF.

14:32.034 --> 14:33.698
JACOB, I'M SO SORRY.

14:33.700 --> 14:36.132
HEY, LOOK, UM...

14:36.134 --> 14:37.732
WOULD YOU CLOSE THAT
DOOR RIGHT THERE BY...

14:37.734 --> 14:40.132
YEAH, NO, THAT'S
THE POINT ACTUALLY.

14:40.134 --> 14:43.998
TASHA, YOU CAN'T --
WE CAN'T.

14:44.000 --> 14:47.332
WHAT HAPPENED BETWEEN US
THE OTHER DAY, THAT KISS,

14:47.334 --> 14:49.465
THAT WAS A MISTAKE.

14:49.467 --> 14:51.932
-IT WAS?
-YEAH.

14:51.934 --> 14:54.265
OKAY, LOOK,
IT WASN'T UNTRUE.

14:54.267 --> 14:56.798
YOU'RE GREAT, YOU'RE
SMART, YOU'RE SEXY,

14:56.800 --> 14:58.732
BUT IT'S JUST,

14:58.734 --> 15:00.398
IT'S NOT SOMETHING I
CAN CHOOSE IN MY LIFE

15:00.400 --> 15:01.865
AT THIS POINT IN TIME.

15:01.867 --> 15:04.132
ME?

15:04.134 --> 15:06.632
YEAH, I'M SORRY.

15:09.934 --> 15:11.332
OKAY.

15:11.334 --> 15:12.465
OKAY, LOOK, PLEASE.

15:12.467 --> 15:16.598
NO, I'M SORRY.
I JUST, UM...

15:16.600 --> 15:19.998
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
STOP TEXTING ME, TOO.

15:20.000 --> 15:22.165
YEAH, I KNOW, THAT WAS
BAD OF ME TO DO THAT.

15:22.167 --> 15:24.432
I JUST, UM...

15:24.434 --> 15:26.899
I MISSED YOU AND I...

15:26.901 --> 15:29.699
TASHA, YOU GOTTA STOP.

15:29.701 --> 15:31.965
PEOPLE ARE GONNA THINK
SOMETHING'S GOING ON.

15:34.267 --> 15:38.932
NOTHING -- NOTHING EVER
SEEMS TO WORK OUT

15:38.934 --> 15:40.732
FOR ME, JACOB.

15:40.734 --> 15:44.132
LIKE, I KNOW THAT
I'M BEING SELFISH,

15:44.134 --> 15:48.965
BUT...I JUST,
I LIKE YOU SO MUCH.

15:48.967 --> 15:51.265
EVERY TIME.

15:51.267 --> 15:54.665
TASHA, LOOK.

15:54.667 --> 15:56.132
COME ON NOW, YOU HAVE
GOT TO PULL IT TOGETHER.

15:56.134 --> 15:57.398
-I CAN'T.
-YOU HAVE TO!

15:57.400 --> 15:58.265
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

15:58.267 --> 16:00.199
I'M YOUR BOSS.
-SERIOUSLY?

16:00.201 --> 16:01.665
PASTOR GREENLEAF,

16:01.667 --> 16:04.665
OH THE SECRETARY TOLD ME THAT
I COULD FIND YOU IN HERE.

16:04.667 --> 16:05.831
IF I'M INTERRUPTING...

16:05.833 --> 16:10.565
NO, POP, WE'RE, UM...
TASHA JUST LOST A FRIEND

16:10.567 --> 16:13.932
AND I WAS...
WE WERE JUST TALKING.

16:13.934 --> 16:15.532
OH, I'M SO SORRY.

16:15.534 --> 16:16.631
THANK YOU.

16:16.633 --> 16:17.899
WHAT BRINGS YOU BY,
POP?

16:17.901 --> 16:20.199
GETTING
MY GRANDDAUGHTER HOME.

16:21.800 --> 16:24.398
RIGHT, HEY, I NEED
TO HANDLE THIS.

16:24.400 --> 16:25.865
YEAH.

16:25.867 --> 16:30.865
ALL RIGHT, PROMISE YOU'RE
GONNA BE OKAY, POSITIVE?

16:30.867 --> 16:34.398
POSITIVE, YOU CAN GO.

16:34.400 --> 16:36.398
ARE YOU TWO SURE I'M NOT
INTERRUPTING ANYTHING?

16:36.400 --> 16:38.732
NO, POP, IT'S FINE.

16:38.734 --> 16:40.398
HOW ABOUT WE GO IN
MY OFFICE AND TALK

16:40.400 --> 16:42.199
AND GIVE HER SOME SPACE?

16:44.134 --> 16:46.998
ABSOLUTELY, UM,

16:47.000 --> 16:48.665
AGAIN I'M SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

16:48.667 --> 16:51.465
THANK YOU, BISHOP.

16:56.467 --> 16:57.532
OPEN OR CLOSED?

16:57.534 --> 16:59.598
CLOSED.

16:59.600 --> 17:07.332
♪♪

17:07.334 --> 17:10.232
[ CRYING ]

17:14.200 --> 17:15.798
HEY, DARLENE,
HOW'S IT GOING?

17:15.800 --> 17:18.598
Darlene: SOMEONE'S
BEEN WAITING A WHILE.

17:18.600 --> 17:21.198
IS THAT
THE DISTRICT ATTORNEY?

17:21.200 --> 17:22.532
CAN YOU JUST
GIVE ME A SECOND?

17:22.534 --> 17:25.065
YEAH,
WHATEVER YOU NEED.

17:30.200 --> 17:32.532
PASTOR GREENLEAF.

17:32.534 --> 17:34.065
DISTRICT ATTORNEY PRICE,

17:34.067 --> 17:36.199
TO WHAT
DO I OWE THIS PLEASURE?

17:36.201 --> 17:38.332
SO YOU DECIDED TO
SUPPORT MISS HUNTER?

17:38.334 --> 17:39.798
I DID, YES.

17:39.800 --> 17:42.532
AGAINST MY STRONGLY
WORDED ADVICE.

17:42.534 --> 17:44.165
I WOULDN'T TAKE THAT
TOO PERSONALLY.

17:44.167 --> 17:45.765
THIS CHURCH IS FULL OF
PEOPLE WHO WOULD TELL YOU

17:45.767 --> 17:48.565
THAT'S JUST HOW I AM.

17:48.567 --> 17:52.165
OH, I MET WITH HER
ATTORNEY, A MR. TELESKA.

17:52.167 --> 17:53.032
WE'RE GETTING HER
A BETTER ONE.

17:53.034 --> 17:54.465
HE SEEMED
PRETTY SHARP TO ME.

17:54.467 --> 17:56.465
I OFFERED HIS CLIENT
A GREAT DEAL.

17:56.467 --> 17:58.732
SHE PLEADS GUILTY TO
SECOND-DEGREE MURDER,

17:58.734 --> 18:00.398
SHE GETS 20 YEARS.

18:00.400 --> 18:01.798
GREAT DEAL.

18:01.800 --> 18:04.098
THIS CASE GOES
TO TRIAL, GRACE,

18:04.100 --> 18:06.465
SHE'LL GET LIFE
WITHOUT PAROLE.

18:06.467 --> 18:10.332
AND YOU MAY FIND
YOURSELF ON TRIAL, TOO,

18:10.334 --> 18:12.865
AND NOT JUST IN THE COURT
OF PUBLIC OPINION.

18:12.867 --> 18:14.065
YOU THREATENING ME?

18:14.067 --> 18:15.798
I COULD HAVE CHARGED
YOU WITH MURDER

18:15.800 --> 18:17.998
WHEN YOU KILLED
YOUR UNCLE.

18:18.000 --> 18:20.398
THE ONLY REASON I
DIDN'T DO THAT WAS --

18:20.400 --> 18:21.632
BECAUSE
IT WAS SELF-DEFENSE.

18:21.634 --> 18:24.865
SO YOU'VE SAID, BUT I
GOT THIS FUNNY FEELING

18:24.867 --> 18:26.865
THAT IF ALL
THE FACTS CAME OUT

18:26.867 --> 18:30.932
ABOUT THE LONG-STANDING FIGHT
BETWEEN YOU AND YOUR UNCLE,

18:30.934 --> 18:34.032
THE DETAILS OF HOW
YOU FORCED YOUR WAY

18:34.034 --> 18:36.465
INTO HIS HOME THAT NIGHT,

18:36.467 --> 18:38.532
YOUR CONCERNS
ABOUT YOUR DAUGHTER

18:38.534 --> 18:41.732
COULD LOOK A LOT LIKE
PREMEDITATED MURDER,

18:41.734 --> 18:43.732
ESPECIALLY TO A JURY
WHO KNEW YOU HAD GONE

18:43.734 --> 18:49.065
OUT OF YOUR WAY TO GET YET
ANOTHER MURDER ACQUITTED.

18:49.067 --> 18:54.065
I MEAN...
PARDON ME FOR SAYING THIS.

18:54.067 --> 18:57.332
I KNOW THIS IS
A RIGHTEOUS TIME FOR LADIES,

18:57.334 --> 18:59.598
BUT, GRACE, I SWEAR,
IT'S STARTING TO LOOK

18:59.600 --> 19:01.332
LIKE YOU THINK
WOMEN SHOULD JUST

19:01.334 --> 19:04.265
BE ABLE TO TAKE THE LAW
INTO THEIR OWN HANDS

19:04.267 --> 19:07.732
AND KILL MEN.

19:07.734 --> 19:09.798
IT JUST DOESN'T SEEM RIGHT,

19:09.800 --> 19:13.732
LEGAL,
OR VERY CHRISTIAN.

19:17.900 --> 19:19.998
HAVE MISS HUNTER
TAKE THE DEAL.

19:20.000 --> 19:26.899
♪♪

19:26.901 --> 19:33.932
♪♪

19:33.934 --> 19:37.398
WHAT DID HE WANT?

19:37.400 --> 19:39.065
NOTHING IMPORTANT.

19:47.233 --> 19:49.265
I REALLY DON'T KNOW

19:49.267 --> 19:52.532
HOW I'M GONNA MAKE IT
WITHOUT HIM.

19:52.534 --> 19:53.532
I DON'T.

19:53.534 --> 19:56.132
[ CRYING ]

20:00.934 --> 20:04.665
THAT'S HOW IT FEELS...

20:04.667 --> 20:08.132
BUT YOU WILL.

20:08.134 --> 20:10.899
YOU'RE GONNA GO ON.

20:17.767 --> 20:19.398
WE ALL DO.

20:19.400 --> 20:21.465
WHAT HE'S OFFERING
IS AN OPTION, CORALIE,

20:21.467 --> 20:22.931
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TAKE IT

20:22.933 --> 20:24.998
AND YOU CERTAINLY DON'T
HAVE TO DECIDE RIGHT NOW.

20:25.000 --> 20:26.232
WE CAN TALK
ABOUT IT LATER.

20:26.234 --> 20:27.565
ARE YOU GONNA LET ME TELL HER
OR NOT?

20:27.567 --> 20:28.931
'CAUSE I DON'T HAVE ALL DAY.

20:28.933 --> 20:31.999
I GOT, LIKE, 12 OTHER CASES
I GOT TO GET TO.

20:32.001 --> 20:33.532
UH-HUH.
GO AHEAD.

20:33.534 --> 20:35.198
LOOK, THE D.A.'S
OFFERING YOU A DEAL.

20:35.200 --> 20:37.465
YOU PLEAD GUILTY
TO SECOND-DEGREE MURDER,

20:37.467 --> 20:38.332
YOU GET 20 YEARS.

20:38.334 --> 20:40.665
WHEN WOULD I GET PAROLED?

20:40.667 --> 20:43.932
15.

20:43.934 --> 20:46.098
THE KIDS
WOULD BE GROWN UP.

20:46.100 --> 20:47.898
LOOK, IT'S EITHER THIS
OR LIFE.

20:47.900 --> 20:49.265
YOU GONNA TAKE IT OR NOT?

20:49.267 --> 20:50.665
IF YOU DON'T HAVE TIME
TO LET HER THINK

20:50.667 --> 20:52.665
FOR ONE MINUTE ABOUT THE
BIGGEST DECISION IN HER LIFE,

20:52.667 --> 20:55.465
YOU SHOULD SURELY LET
SOMEONE ELSE REPRESENT HER.

20:55.467 --> 20:56.865
SHE'S A VICTIM OF ABUSE.

20:56.867 --> 20:58.132
SHE DOESN'T EVEN
REMEMBER DOING IT.

20:58.134 --> 20:59.332
THERE ARE PRECEDENTS
FOR THAT.

20:59.334 --> 21:01.265
YEAH, WELL, NOT IN MEMPHIS,
AND I KNOW THIS JUDGE,

21:01.267 --> 21:03.598
AND HE'S NOT EXACTLY A FAN
OF THIS WHOLE ME TOO MOVEMENT.

21:03.600 --> 21:07.698
LOOK, JUST TAKE THE DEAL,
AND YOUR KIDS WILL VISIT.

21:07.700 --> 21:09.832
I GOTTA THINK ABOUT IT.

21:09.834 --> 21:11.565
ALL RIGHT, WELL, YOU'VE GOT
TILL TOMORROW TO DECIDE,

21:11.567 --> 21:13.398
SO IF YOU FOLKS WILL EXCUSE ME,

21:13.400 --> 21:14.865
I'VE GOT TO GET TO PLACES

21:14.867 --> 21:17.565
WHERE MY WORK'S
A LITTLE MORE APPRECIATED.

21:21.734 --> 21:22.665
YOU CAN DO BETTER.

21:22.667 --> 21:23.998
YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

21:24.000 --> 21:27.332
YOU CAN CERTAINLY
DO BETTER THAN HIM.

21:27.334 --> 21:29.465
-GOOD NEWS.
-TELL ME.

21:29.467 --> 21:31.065
I GOT YOU A VISIT
WITH YOUR KIDS.

21:31.067 --> 21:31.998
WHEN?

21:32.000 --> 21:33.065
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY NOW.

21:33.067 --> 21:35.532
OH, MY GOD, THANK YOU,
THANK YOU.

21:35.534 --> 21:39.732
YOU'RE AN ANGEL.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

21:39.734 --> 21:41.265
[ LAUGHING ]

21:41.267 --> 21:42.798
PICK UP THE PHONE
AND CALL HIM!

21:42.800 --> 21:44.998
POP, WHAT DO YOU THINK
SKIP'S GONNA DO?

21:45.000 --> 21:47.865
HE'LL HAVE THE POLICE
PICK THE BOY UP.

21:47.867 --> 21:49.198
SHE'S AN ADULT.

21:49.200 --> 21:51.332
SHE LEFT
OF HER OWN FREE WILL.

21:51.334 --> 21:53.132
ALL RIGHT, I MEAN, IT'S --

21:53.134 --> 21:54.598
THIS ISN'T SOMETHING
YOU CAN FIX

21:54.600 --> 21:57.065
WITH A PHONE CALL TO
SOME FRIEND IN AN OFFICE.

21:57.067 --> 21:58.665
WE HAVE TO DO SOMETHING!

21:58.667 --> 22:00.398
THERE'S NOTHING TO DO.

22:00.400 --> 22:04.465
AND EVEN IF THERE WAS, NOBODY
WANTS US TO DO IT, POP.

22:04.467 --> 22:06.199
I KNOW YOU'RE UPSET THAT
MAMA DIDN'T CALL YOU,

22:06.201 --> 22:07.798
BUT THIS ISN'T YOUR PROBLEM

22:07.800 --> 22:10.332
AND ACCORDING TO MY WIFE,
IT'S NOT EVEN MINE.

22:10.334 --> 22:12.465
SO JUST DO US BOTH A FAVOR
AND GO BACK TO PERCY'S

22:12.467 --> 22:14.732
OR CHURCH OR WHEREVER,
BUT STAY OUT OF IT.

22:14.734 --> 22:16.932
I'VE GOT ENOUGH ON MY PLATE
WITHOUT TRYING TO MAKE

22:16.934 --> 22:19.399
YOU FEEL LIKE YOU'RE
SOME BIG HELP, TOO.

22:24.600 --> 22:26.265
[ SIGHS ]

22:26.267 --> 22:28.932
YOU KNOW,

22:28.934 --> 22:33.865
KERISSA WASN'T WRONG
TO SEND YOU AWAY.

22:33.867 --> 22:38.265
THAT TEMPER OF YOURS
IS NO HELP TO ANYONE,

22:38.267 --> 22:40.265
ESPECIALLY YOU.

22:44.400 --> 22:46.532
WHATEVER HAPPENED
BETWEEN ME AND YOUR MAMA,

22:46.534 --> 22:49.465
I'M STILL YOUR FATHER AND
THAT GIRL'S GRANDFATHER.

22:52.800 --> 22:57.099
WHEN YOU REMEMBER THAT,
CALL ME.

23:03.934 --> 23:05.598
SO WHO IS YOUR FRIEND
AT CPS?

23:05.600 --> 23:08.332
YOU HAVEN'T LET THAT
GO YET, HAVE YOU?

23:08.334 --> 23:09.598
IT'S A NATURAL
QUESTION.

23:09.600 --> 23:10.732
I'M JUST WAITING
FOR A NATURAL ANSWER.

23:10.734 --> 23:13.665
AFTER ALL I'VE DONE.

23:13.667 --> 23:16.398
GAVE YOU THIS MONEY,
MADE THE PHONE CALLS,

23:16.400 --> 23:17.499
YOU STILL DON'T TRUST ME.

23:17.501 --> 23:19.865
WHO IS SHE?

23:19.867 --> 23:21.732
I MET HER
THROUGH BIG SISTERS.

23:21.734 --> 23:23.265
YOU WORK WITH THEM,
TOO?

23:23.267 --> 23:25.332
I WAS ONE.

23:25.334 --> 23:26.865
YOU WERE A BIG SISTER?

23:26.867 --> 23:28.998
YES.

23:29.000 --> 23:32.798
I'VE GOT FOUR GIRLS OUT
THERE RUNNING THE WORLD.

23:32.800 --> 23:35.065
I HIT 'EM UP FOR
FAVORS SOMETIMES.

23:36.867 --> 23:37.998
I'M NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

23:38.000 --> 23:39.165
THEN WHAT ARE YOU?

23:39.167 --> 23:41.699
I'M JUST LIKE YOU,
GRACE,

23:41.701 --> 23:43.998
SOMEONE WHO NO MATTER
HOW HIGH I RISE,

23:44.000 --> 23:46.998
NO MATTER HOW WELL I DO,

23:47.000 --> 23:51.332
I CAN'T HELP BUT TO SEE
MYSELF IN LOW, LOST SOULS.

23:51.334 --> 23:54.665
AND JUST LIKE YOU,
I WON'T STOP FIGHTING

23:54.667 --> 23:57.265
TILL ALL THE FOLKS
WHO KEEP THEM DOWN

23:57.267 --> 23:59.199
ARE BROUGHT LOW, TOO.

24:01.067 --> 24:03.732
THAT SOUNDS
A LOT LIKE REVENGE.

24:03.734 --> 24:07.132
WELL, MAYBE THE D.A.
WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU.

24:07.134 --> 24:09.332
I JUST SEE IT
AS JUSTICE.

24:09.334 --> 24:14.832
♪♪

24:14.834 --> 24:20.598
♪♪

24:20.600 --> 24:22.265
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

24:22.267 --> 24:25.798
OKAY?

24:25.800 --> 24:28.598
HOW'D IT GO?

24:28.600 --> 24:30.932
I CAN'T GO TO PRISON.

24:30.934 --> 24:32.732
I WON'T.

24:32.734 --> 24:34.332
GOOD.

24:34.334 --> 24:37.365
HEY.

24:37.367 --> 24:42.998
♪♪

24:43.000 --> 24:48.465
♪♪

24:48.467 --> 24:50.332
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

24:50.334 --> 24:51.665
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

24:51.667 --> 24:53.432
YEAH?

24:57.234 --> 25:00.032
THIS JUST CAME FOR YOU.

25:00.034 --> 25:02.165
-THANK YOU.
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

25:24.867 --> 25:34.965
♪♪

25:34.967 --> 25:44.865
♪♪

25:44.867 --> 25:48.365
♪♪

25:50.534 --> 25:52.598
Kerissa: THAT'S THEM.

25:52.600 --> 25:54.032
Mae: WHAT?

25:56.101 --> 25:57.099
I'M COMING, TOO.

25:57.101 --> 25:59.765
NO, PLEASE, MAE, DON'T.

25:59.767 --> 26:01.865
I HAVE TO DO THIS ALONE.

26:08.633 --> 26:09.899
♪ TO BE A LYRICIST TAKES
DILIGENCE, BELIEVE ME ♪

26:13.534 --> 26:15.465
LEAVE ME ALONE.

26:15.467 --> 26:16.731
I HAVE SOMETHING
I WANT TO SAY.

26:16.733 --> 26:18.432
THE LAST THING I NEED
IS FOR YOU TO BE HERE

26:18.434 --> 26:19.632
WHEN HE GETS BACK.

26:19.634 --> 26:21.999
JUST LISTEN TO ME
FOR A MINUTE.

26:24.467 --> 26:26.632
OKAY, ONE MINUTE.

26:31.200 --> 26:33.332
[ SIGHS ]

26:33.334 --> 26:34.932
WHAT?

26:37.067 --> 26:38.531
DO YOU KNOW THE DAY
YOU WERE BORN,

26:38.533 --> 26:41.299
I DIDN'T HAVE A WORD TO
DESCRIBE WHAT YOU WERE TO ME?

26:41.301 --> 26:43.765
YOU WERE EVERYTHING,
MORE THAN THE WORLD.

26:43.767 --> 26:46.565
THEY CLEANED YOU OFF AND
THEY PUT YOU IN MY ARMS

26:46.567 --> 26:48.665
AND YOU JUST
LOOKED AT ME.

26:48.667 --> 26:50.198
YOU WEREN'T FLAILING
OR CRYING

26:50.200 --> 26:51.798
OR DOING ANYTHING THAT
I THOUGHT YOU SHOULD BE,

26:51.800 --> 26:53.198
YOU WERE JUST
LOOKING UP AT ME

26:53.200 --> 26:55.198
WITH THOSE WIDE,
BROWN EYES.

26:55.200 --> 26:58.732
HURRY UP.

26:58.734 --> 26:59.865
WHERE ARE YOU TWO GOING?

26:59.867 --> 27:01.265
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

27:01.267 --> 27:06.465
JUST SAY WHAT YOU
HAVE TO SAY, PLEASE.

27:06.467 --> 27:08.865
I WANTED YOU TO
SEE THE WORLD, ZORA.

27:08.867 --> 27:10.398
I WANTED YOU
TO GO TO COLLEGE.

27:10.400 --> 27:13.465
I WANTED YOU TO FIND OUT WHAT
YOU WERE PASSIONATE ABOUT,

27:13.467 --> 27:16.231
AND I'M SORRY
IF YOU EVER FELT BEAT DOWN

27:16.233 --> 27:17.299
BY MY EXPECTATIONS.

27:17.301 --> 27:19.698
IT WAS BECAUSE OF THE WAY
THAT YOU LOOKED AT ME

27:19.700 --> 27:23.832
ON THE DAY THAT YOU WERE BORN
WITH YOUR OWN EXPECTATIONS.

27:23.834 --> 27:27.532
I COULD SEE IN YOU
ALL OF THE DESIRE

27:27.534 --> 27:30.798
THAT YOU HAD FOR YOUR LIFE
AND I WANTED TO GIVE YOU

27:30.800 --> 27:32.132
EVERY SINGLE TOOL AT
YOUR DISPOSAL

27:32.134 --> 27:34.198
SO THAT YOU COULD GO OUT
INTO THE WORLD AND GET IT.

27:34.200 --> 27:35.398
AND I'VE GOT IT.

27:35.400 --> 27:37.332
WHAT DO YOU HAVE?

27:37.334 --> 27:40.131
YOU GOT A BOY
THAT BEATS YOU UP,

27:40.133 --> 27:41.399
A ONE-WAY TICKET
TO NOWHERE.

27:41.401 --> 27:42.998
I'VE GOT MYSELF.

27:43.000 --> 27:46.499
LOOK, WHY IS THAT SO HARD
FOR YOU TO UNDERSTAND?

27:50.400 --> 27:53.798
ZORA...

27:53.800 --> 27:56.665
THIS IS IT.

27:56.667 --> 28:00.998
YOU CAN GET OUT OF THIS CAR
AND COME WITH ME RIGHT NOW

28:01.000 --> 28:03.798
BECAUSE THIS IS THE LAST
CHANCE THAT I'M GONNA GIVE YOU.

28:03.800 --> 28:06.031
AFTER THIS,
IT IS GONNA BE YOU,

28:06.033 --> 28:08.498
YOUR BAD DECISIONS,
AND GOD.

28:08.500 --> 28:11.232
AND GOD IS GONNA WIN

28:11.234 --> 28:13.732
'CAUSE IN SITUATIONS
LIKE THIS, HONEY,

28:13.734 --> 28:17.865
HE IS A LOT TOUGHER
THAN ME.

28:17.867 --> 28:20.399
I'LL TAKE MY CHANCES.

28:20.401 --> 28:30.565
♪♪

28:30.567 --> 28:40.532
♪♪

28:40.534 --> 28:50.198
♪♪

28:50.200 --> 28:53.198
♪♪

28:53.200 --> 28:54.565
[ SNIFFLES ]

29:13.200 --> 29:14.999
[ HORN HONKING ]

29:26.800 --> 29:29.432
[ KEYPAD BEEPING ]

29:40.500 --> 29:43.398
MUILLARD!

29:43.400 --> 29:46.465
WHY ISN'T THE GATE OPENING?

29:46.467 --> 29:48.165
ARE YOU KIDD--

29:55.467 --> 29:57.198
MAE?

29:57.200 --> 29:58.665
MAE?

29:58.667 --> 30:08.798
♪♪

30:08.800 --> 30:11.731
YOU CHANGED
THE GATE CODE?

30:11.733 --> 30:13.532
WHAT DO YOU WANT,
JAMES?

30:13.534 --> 30:15.599
OH, I'LL TELL YA.

30:24.267 --> 30:25.265
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

30:25.267 --> 30:27.332
HEY, YOU GOT A SECOND?

30:27.334 --> 30:29.465
NOT REALLY.

30:29.467 --> 30:32.532
MY UBER'S GONNA BE
HERE ANY MINUTE.

30:32.534 --> 30:36.865
WELL, THAT MEANS YOU'VE GOT
ABOUT 10 MINUTES THEN, RIGHT?

30:36.867 --> 30:40.398
WHAT DO YOU WANT,
JACOB?

30:40.400 --> 30:42.932
I JUST WANTED TO
APOLOGIZE, ALL RIGHT?

30:42.934 --> 30:45.065
I KNOW THAT THING I SAID
ABOUT BEING YOUR BOSS

30:45.067 --> 30:48.165
WAS KIND OF
A STUPID THING TO SAY.

30:48.167 --> 30:49.365
YEAH.

30:49.367 --> 30:50.832
I'M ANGRY
ABOUT ZORA LEAVING,

30:50.834 --> 30:52.765
AND I FEEL LIKE
IT'S MY FAULT,

30:52.767 --> 30:53.965
BUT I CAN'T TELL
KERISSA THAT

30:53.967 --> 30:55.365
BECAUSE I KNOW IT'S
WHAT SHE ALREADY THINKS

30:55.367 --> 30:57.898
AND I HATE THAT,
I HATE THAT SHE'S RIGHT.

30:57.900 --> 30:59.365
LOOK, I TOOK IT OUT ON YOU

30:59.367 --> 31:02.298
AND IT DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING
TO DO WITH YOU AND I'M SORRY.

31:02.300 --> 31:05.765
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR SAYING SO.

31:05.767 --> 31:08.265
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

31:08.267 --> 31:10.998
UM, MY CAR IS HERE

31:11.000 --> 31:14.632
SO I'M GONNA GO.

31:16.534 --> 31:18.998
WAIT A MINUTE.

31:19.000 --> 31:20.598
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:20.600 --> 31:21.598
WHAT DOES IT LOOK LIKE?

31:21.600 --> 31:23.398
WHAT, ARE YOU QUITTING?

31:23.400 --> 31:24.332
UH, YEAH.

31:24.334 --> 31:25.499
WHY,
BECAUSE OF WHAT I SAID?

31:25.501 --> 31:28.165
NO, BECAUSE I DON'T
BELONG HERE, JACOB!

31:28.167 --> 31:30.031
I SHOULD HAVE LEFT
WHEN BASIE LEFT,

31:30.033 --> 31:32.498
BUT I DECIDED TO STAY
BECAUSE I LIKED YOU.

31:32.500 --> 31:35.098
AND NOW I LIKE YOU A LOT
MORE THAN JUST LIKING,

31:35.100 --> 31:36.732
I GOTTA GO.

31:36.734 --> 31:40.598
TASHA, JUST...
JUST SLOW DOWN.

31:40.600 --> 31:42.398
I WANT YOU HERE.

31:42.400 --> 31:46.598
I KNOW YOU DO,
BUT THAT CAN'T MATTER TO ME

31:46.600 --> 31:48.065
BECAUSE IT'S NOT GOOD
FOR ME.

31:48.067 --> 31:50.265
IT'S NOT THE ANSWER.

31:50.267 --> 31:51.732
YOU'RE MARRIED.

31:51.734 --> 31:53.865
I'M STILL TECHNICALLY
MARRIED TO BASIE,

31:53.867 --> 31:56.065
WHEREVER HE IS OR ISN'T.

31:56.067 --> 31:58.265
AND ZORA, IT'S JUST --

31:58.267 --> 32:01.198
TRUST ME,
IT'S FOR THE BEST.

32:01.200 --> 32:03.199
COME ON, TASHA.

32:06.467 --> 32:09.132
JUST KNOW
THAT I'M SORRY.

32:09.134 --> 32:10.865
FOR WHAT?

32:10.867 --> 32:13.598
FOR EVERYTHING.

32:13.600 --> 32:21.732
♪♪

32:21.734 --> 32:24.065
CHARITY,
BEFORE YOU GO...

32:24.067 --> 32:26.798
I TOLD YOU
THAT ISN'T NECESSARY.

32:26.800 --> 32:28.865
A LABORER
IS WORTHY OF HIS HIRE.

32:28.867 --> 32:30.398
NOW, DIDN'T YOUR DADDY
TEACH YOU THAT?

32:30.400 --> 32:32.232
YOU KNOW WHAT? FOR SOMEONE
WHO DON'T GO TO CHURCH,

32:32.234 --> 32:33.465
YOU REALLY KNOW
YOUR BIBLE.

32:33.467 --> 32:34.598
WELL, I MAY NOT
GO TO CHURCH,

32:34.600 --> 32:37.332
BUT I ATTEND
A LOT OF FUNERALS.

32:37.334 --> 32:41.132
I GUESS THERE'S ABOUT
10 PAGES I KNOW BY HEART.

32:41.134 --> 32:42.665
LET'S HOPE IT GETS
YOU INTO HEAVEN.

32:42.667 --> 32:44.598
I'M MORE WORRIED
ABOUT EARTH.

32:44.600 --> 32:46.265
WELL, WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

32:46.267 --> 32:50.598
YOU GOT A GIFT FOR THIS,
NOW, YOU KNOW, DON'T YA?

32:50.600 --> 32:52.398
YEAH, YOU DO.

32:52.400 --> 32:54.132
A GIFT FOR WHAT,
SINGING?

32:54.134 --> 32:57.665
NO, THIS WORK,
COMFORTING PEOPLE.

32:57.667 --> 33:00.665
SOME FOLKS, THEY CLAM
UP AROUND GRIEF,

33:00.667 --> 33:01.932
OTHER FOLKS
CAN'T SHUT UP,

33:01.934 --> 33:03.332
FAMILIES
CAN'T GET A WORD IN,

33:03.334 --> 33:05.998
BUT YOU, YOU KNOW
JUST WHAT TO SAY

33:06.000 --> 33:08.798
AND WHAT NOT TO SAY,
BUT BEST OF ALL, NOW,

33:08.800 --> 33:11.732
THERE'S -- THERE'S YOU.

33:11.734 --> 33:13.765
-ME?
-IT'S JUST A THING.

33:13.767 --> 33:15.631
SOME FOLKS GOT IT,
SOME DON'T.

33:15.633 --> 33:18.332
YOU GOT IT.

33:18.334 --> 33:20.332
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR SAYING SO.

33:20.334 --> 33:23.265
WHAT DO YOU, UH,

33:23.267 --> 33:25.598
WHAT DO YOU SAY
TO A JOB?

33:25.600 --> 33:29.732
A JOB?
DOING WHAT, THIS?

33:29.734 --> 33:31.732
YEAH, YOU KNOW, I'VE NEVER MET
ANYBODY BEFORE

33:31.734 --> 33:33.932
WHO COULD TAKE OVER.

33:33.934 --> 33:35.031
YOU CAN.

33:35.033 --> 33:36.898
WOULD YOU THINK ABOUT IT?

33:36.900 --> 33:38.298
PERCY.

33:38.300 --> 33:39.731
I'M GONNA BE GONE SOON.

33:39.733 --> 33:41.865
I NEED SOMEBODY
TO RUN THIS PLACE.

33:41.867 --> 33:43.798
YOU'RE GONNA BE
AROUND FOR A LONG TIME,

33:43.800 --> 33:45.399
SO STOP TALKING
LIKE THAT.

33:45.401 --> 33:46.865
THINK ABOUT IT.

33:49.467 --> 33:51.399
THANK YOU FOR ASKING.

33:55.400 --> 33:57.299
REALLY.

33:57.301 --> 34:03.965
IT MEANS A LOT TO BE SEEN
AND VALUED,

34:03.967 --> 34:06.798
BUT I COULDN'T DO THIS
EVERY DAY.

34:06.800 --> 34:08.831
I'M NOT STRONG
ENOUGH YET.

34:08.833 --> 34:10.832
YOU'RE STRONGER
THAN YOU THINK.

34:14.434 --> 34:17.432
BYE, PERCY,

34:17.434 --> 34:18.999
AND THANK YOU.

34:25.000 --> 34:26.631
AND THEN SHE TELLS ME
THAT MY GRANDBABY

34:26.633 --> 34:30.632
HAS LEFT HOME YET AGAIN
WITH THAT BOY WHO BEATS HER.

34:30.634 --> 34:32.565
IT SOUNDS TO ME LIKE
YOU'RE MORE UPSET

34:32.567 --> 34:33.965
ABOUT NOT BEING CONSULTED

34:33.967 --> 34:35.832
THAN YOU ARE THAT
THE GIRL UP AND LEFT.

34:35.834 --> 34:37.932
MAE, I'VE BEEN TRYING ALL DAY
TO GET THAT GIRL BACK HOME

34:37.934 --> 34:38.932
AND I PROBABLY
COULD HAVE DONE IT

34:38.934 --> 34:41.998
IF YOU HAD JUST
DIALED ME IN.

34:42.000 --> 34:43.398
I AM STILL THE HEAD
OF THIS FAMILY.

34:43.400 --> 34:45.132
YOU ARE
THE HEAD OF NOTHING

34:45.134 --> 34:47.798
EXCEPT YOUR OWN
SILLY SELF, MISTER.

34:47.800 --> 34:49.932
EXCEPT MAYBE THAT PILE
OF SAGGY CORNBREAD

34:49.934 --> 34:53.599
AND PANTYHOSE THAT
YOU GAVE MY MONEY TO.

34:55.267 --> 34:59.265
AND NOT TO MENTION,
JAMES, THAT I,

34:59.267 --> 35:03.865
ME ALONE, I AM
THE SOLE PROPRIETOR,

35:03.867 --> 35:06.265
THE CHIEF COOK
AND BOTTLE WASHER,

35:06.267 --> 35:08.699
SOMETIMES BABYSITTER,
CHAUFFEUR, PASTOR

35:08.701 --> 35:11.565
AND, YES, HEAD SHRINKER
FOR ALL YOUR CHILDREN

35:11.567 --> 35:12.898
AND ALL THE SORRY SOULS

35:12.900 --> 35:14.632
THAT THEY'VE DRAWN
TO THEMSELVES

35:14.634 --> 35:17.565
WITH THEIR GREENLEAF
GRAVITY, SO, YES, I AM SORRY

35:17.567 --> 35:22.232
THAT I DID NOT ALSO GET YOU
YOUR STATUS REPORT, SIR.

35:24.534 --> 35:26.732
OH, JAMES.

35:26.734 --> 35:30.365
IF YOU HAD
JUST BEEN PATIENT...

35:33.334 --> 35:35.465
...AND WAITED WHILE
I FOUND THE STRENGTH

35:35.467 --> 35:36.665
TO TAKE YOU BACK,

35:36.667 --> 35:38.932
WE WOULD HAVE BEEN BY
EACH OTHER'S SIDE TODAY.

35:38.934 --> 35:41.065
ALL I'M ASKING IS
YOUR ASSISTANCE

35:41.067 --> 35:42.865
IN REMINDING THESE
CHILDREN THAT I EXIST.

35:42.867 --> 35:45.665
OH, JAMES,
THEY KNOW YOU EXIST,

35:45.667 --> 35:48.265
BUT HAVING FAILED
THEM AS WE HAVE,

35:48.267 --> 35:50.465
AND, YES,
I SHARE THE BLAME,

35:50.467 --> 35:52.798
WE BOTH EXIST
LIKE, I DON'T KNOW,

35:52.800 --> 35:56.065
TWO FADED STARS THAT
WENT OUT LONG AGO

35:56.067 --> 35:59.532
AND ONLY GLOW LIKE GHOSTS.

35:59.534 --> 36:02.065
YOU CAN SOOTHE YOURSELF
WITH THAT POETRY.

36:02.067 --> 36:03.732
YOU'RE IN THIS HOUSE.

36:03.734 --> 36:06.532
YES, I AM,
AND YOU'RE NOT,

36:06.534 --> 36:09.098
AND YOU CAN'T AND BELIEVE IT
OR NOT,

36:09.100 --> 36:14.332
FOR THAT, JAMES,
YOU HAVE MY SYMPATHY.

36:14.334 --> 36:16.265
A LOT OF GOOD
THAT DOES ME.

36:16.267 --> 36:18.998
SYMPATHY IS NOT
A CURRENCY, JAMES.

36:19.000 --> 36:23.198
IT IS NOT TO BE TRADED,
IT IS A FEELING.

36:23.200 --> 36:29.265
♪♪

36:29.267 --> 36:30.598
IF YOU WANT A FRIEND,

36:30.600 --> 36:33.465
YOU JUST...

36:33.467 --> 36:35.799
TALK TO JESUS.

36:40.467 --> 36:42.832
[ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING ]

36:42.834 --> 36:46.532
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

36:52.267 --> 36:53.598
[ SIGHS ]

36:53.600 --> 36:55.865
K?

36:55.867 --> 36:58.332
BABY?

37:04.034 --> 37:06.265
HEY.

37:06.267 --> 37:07.932
OH, I DIDN'T
MAKE DINNER.

37:07.934 --> 37:10.665
I DON'T CARE ABOUT THAT.

37:10.667 --> 37:13.331
IS WINKIE DOWN?

37:13.333 --> 37:16.832
YEAH,
I JUST TUCKED HIM IN.

37:19.800 --> 37:25.065
SO WHAT HAPPENED,
DID YOU GO OVER THERE?

37:25.067 --> 37:26.465
YEAH.

37:26.467 --> 37:29.332
AND?

37:29.334 --> 37:35.665
♪♪

37:35.667 --> 37:38.065
OUR LITTLE GIRL
IS GONE.

37:38.067 --> 37:47.999
♪♪

37:48.001 --> 37:52.932
♪♪

37:52.934 --> 37:57.999
♪♪

38:10.134 --> 38:13.665
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

38:22.134 --> 38:24.598
CHILLING IN THE DARK?

38:24.600 --> 38:26.532
YEAH.

38:30.934 --> 38:32.265
MOM?

38:32.267 --> 38:33.499
MM.

38:33.501 --> 38:36.465
I DON'T WANT
TO GO TO RHODES.

38:36.467 --> 38:39.865
OKAY, BUT YOU'RE
GOING TO COLLEGE.

38:39.867 --> 38:41.665
ZORA'S NOT GOING
TO COLLEGE.

38:41.667 --> 38:43.532
YOU'RE NOT ZORA.

38:43.534 --> 38:45.132
SO ZORA GETS TO DO
WHATEVER SHE WANTS,

38:45.134 --> 38:46.132
MOVE OUT, QUIT SCHOOL.

38:46.134 --> 38:47.198
BABY, SHE'S 18.

38:47.200 --> 38:49.431
YEAH, AND I'LL BE
18 SOON, TOO.

38:49.433 --> 38:51.499
YOU CAN'T FORCE ME
TO GO THERE.

38:51.501 --> 38:54.331
I WASN'T GONNA FORCE
YOU TO DO ANYTHING.

38:54.333 --> 38:56.299
GOOD.

38:58.534 --> 39:00.265
[ SIGHS ]

39:00.267 --> 39:02.398
I DON'T WANT TO GO
TO A CHRISTIAN SCHOOL.

39:02.400 --> 39:06.098
IT'S JUST NOT
WHERE I'M AT RIGHT NOW.

39:06.100 --> 39:08.232
UNDERSTOOD.

39:33.567 --> 39:35.831
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP
SO EARLY?

39:35.833 --> 39:38.165
I HAVEN'T BEEN
TO SLEEP YET.

39:38.167 --> 39:39.832
WELL, THAT'S A LOT
OF NO SLEEPING

39:39.834 --> 39:43.132
FOR A MAN WITH NO
SECOND THOUGHTS.

39:43.134 --> 39:45.265
I KNOW.

39:45.267 --> 39:48.332
MAYBE A RECORD.

39:48.334 --> 39:52.065
YOU KNOW, SOME PEOPLE
GOT FORETHOUGHT.

39:52.067 --> 39:53.732
THEY GOT ENOUGH SENSE
TO MOVE OUT OF THE WAY

39:53.734 --> 39:55.965
WHEN A TRUCK IS COMING.

39:57.400 --> 40:00.732
OTHER PEOPLE
GOT HINDSIGHT.

40:00.734 --> 40:02.998
BEST THING THEY CAN DO
IS GET THE LICENSE NUMBER

40:03.000 --> 40:06.798
AFTER THEY GET RUN OVER.

40:06.800 --> 40:10.598
SOME PEOPLE GOT NEITHER.

40:10.600 --> 40:14.265
JIMMY, AT LEAST
YOU GOT ONE.

40:14.267 --> 40:20.398
♪♪

40:20.400 --> 40:26.398
♪♪

40:26.400 --> 40:30.332
NOT MY WILL,
BUT THY WILL, LORD.

40:30.334 --> 40:35.565
NOTHING MORE, NOTHING LESS...

40:35.567 --> 40:38.265
AND NOTHING ELSE.

40:38.267 --> 40:48.199
♪♪

40:48.201 --> 40:58.132
♪♪

40:58.134 --> 41:08.132
♪♪

41:08.134 --> 41:17.832
♪♪

41:17.834 --> 41:25.065
♪♪
